,Recommended,294370,24291894,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,Princess Gay X,"What a gem! Crowntakers is straight up 7/10 in its genre.I bought the game for during 25% off sale, and I must say I wasnt disappointed. On average you would probably spend about 10 hours in game anyway.Pretty graphics and somewhat easy to understand game mechanics take you in pretty quickly. It takes about 15 minutes to understand how to fight and not lose and maybe about an hour that there are actually ways to beat the game in efficient way. All comes down to how random this game is, your strategy will depend on it and it will eventually decide the outcome at the end.Fighting mechanics are very easy to understand. Game mechanics are pretty simple too, all you need to worry about is how many turns you have left. Now, I have actually never finished a game in normal mode ( it was actually called hard before) and only won ( saved the king) on easy. Modes are not so different, but on normal you can only rely on yourself, you can hardly build strategy on the go, unless you get very lucky. Yes, a lot in this game comes down to how you will get lucky or unlucky with the choice of items, skills or mercenaries.The sound is really well made. Very simple music fits the game just right. I will not spoil you experience. Other sound effects good too, everything makes the sound its supposed to make.Graphics are simple yet very attractive. I am not sure if this game was ever on a tablet, but that is the kind of graphics is has. Simple and effective and everyone can run it on their low end computer. What else do you need from a game like this?Now, what really has me going is how random this can be. I understand that is a part of the game, but boy does it make me mad sometimes. You will be enraged on occasions when things just do go your way. Fighting can be annoying too, you will be misclicking quite a lot and that might cost you dearly. Oh, and no saves, you die - you lose!The game has some basic story with its plot twist at the end, but thats about it. You dont expect a story from a board game do you? This is just the same.In the end, this game is worth buying almost at a full price. Replayablility is high as every character has 3 different sets of abilities. The game is not extremely addictive, but you would not expect that. This game will let you do simple strategy moves and relax at the same time. If you are up for challenge in both game and yourself, then this game is for you."
