76561198041593195,Recommended,294370,17805917,"Posted: 30 August, 2015",all,wyndigo,"Crowntakers is a a casual, colorful tactical turn based game.  I thought I would give it a try...and was really surprised by how many great game design choices the developers made!Examples of great game design:+ Every map is randomized - not only the map layout, but also your units' positions!+ The fight is not going well and you're in a bind.  Do you use potions now or save them for a later fight?+ Mercenaries have different abilities, and choosing which mercs to use (and their variant skills) and building combos make it fun and replayable+ Normal is quite difficult, so the ability to carry over experience after defeat in Easy mode is a great option.  (I was able to beat the game in my 2nd easy playthrough, but it was close!)+ Runes for your fighters have good variety - enough to make choosing which merc gets which runes important for battles.+ A new merc can be unlocked with each playthrough, which incentivizes playing it again and again, even if you've won already (winning one time through might only take 3-4 hours)+ Your hero and each merc have unlockable skills. To unlock them you have to do perform various feats with each hero, which incentivizes you to change your tactics each playthrough.+ On the main map, at each cave/house/roundtower/etc, you can only choose to perform one action out of 2-5 options. Once you've done the action, you have to live with your choice!  On the next playthrough, you can choose differently...+ There is a trade-off between spending time searching all the houses, caves, etc, and progressing through the map.  Every night it says ""another night has past, your enemies have gotten stronger"".  It's another design element to force the user to choose a strategy.+ The user interface, menus and buttons have a good layout and are pretty intuitive.+ The encounter stories are entertaining.  They are short vignettes, entirely appropriate for the casual theme.Overall, very impressed with the design elements, as well as the bright colorful art.  I already want to play this developer's next game, too!"
