76561198042874671,Recommended,294370,12940812,"Posted: 14 November, 2014",all,Mumbo,"After reading some of the other reviews, I decided to post my opinion.Why this game is good:-Mechanics that are easy to understand but can be used in creative and various ways.-The art, music, and tone of the game is consistent and engaging.-The combat requires actual elements of strategy (considering your opponents move, your position, your resources)-on this note, the majority of bosses are a pleasure (a frustrating pleasure) to fight.-The random events can be interesting at times-Each play through has a good amount of varietyWhere the game falls short-The random events don't have much variety-most of them are search and most of the time you'll get stuff, sometimes you'll get hurt-RNG sometimes doesn't make sense (Ex. a chest in the first area, but no possible way to have/get a lockpick)-While very interesting, playing through the whole campaign felt too shortNeutral points-RNG is RNG: while I have been rekt by it on occasion, sometimes its forgiving. It wouldn't be ""RNG"" if it were ""balanced"", RNG implies randomness which is not solely dependent on ""fairness"" ( you can flip a coin 50 times and get 50 heads).That being said, if there were ever a Crowntakers2 or DLC to extend the campaign (or institute a new one) I would buy it. -I also feel like this game could have an interesting multiplayer mode if developed.-Feels short, but then again theres a lot of content that justifies the $15 price tagRegarding some of the individual grievances against the game:Firstly, saying that this game is meant for you to fail before you succeed is incorrect.While this seems like the case in easy mode, easy mode is more of a way for you to learn and understand the true nature of the mechanics, specifically how the mercenaries work together and their individual skills. You can do a lot by combining the different skills of the mercenaries in different conformations. Another key aspect of this game is that it has a lot to do with positioning in combat. Often, people don't understand this and charge in meaninglessly. This difficulty isn't manufactured, it is intrinsic in the games design. Thinking of how you will position yourself for the enemy's phase is often more challenging than deciding what moves you want to make on your turn (which also is considerably difficult). Also, fighting thieves work on the former mechanic much more than the latter (and you can definitely win without losing anyone). While you will likely die because of your incorrect choices and on part because of the RNG, it is ultimately up to you to consider which choices are risky and which aren't.All that being said, it is entirely possible for you to succeed on the first playthrough if you fully understand the games mechanics and strategy. I won't say its likely, but it was designed so that you can progress (from level 1) all the way to the castle in one sitting, because normal mode is beatable.The game is not grinding based (once again, because normal mode is a thing) although you will need to if you want to unlock some of the different mercenary stages (which have no impact on your ability to beat the game, just your method of beating it).I'm not gonna address the QQ ""errybody conters cept me"" responses when the game hasn't been played for more than a couple hours."
